parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the front brake lever to become rock hard and unusable, leading to a complete loss of brakes, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The front brake lever becomes stiff or hard to pull
the front brake lever is unable to be pulled
the ABS system fails to revert to non-ABS mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the foot shifter arm can cause the shifter to become loose or fall off, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, especially when downshifting or braking, which can result in accidents or serious injuries.
symptoms: the shifter arm slips away from the transmission
the shifter arm slides up and down the splined shaft
the entire foot shifter is missing
the vehicle is stuck in gear

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Sidewall Cracking on Harley-Davidson Dunlop Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature sidewall cracking on the front tires can lead to a loss of tire pressure, reduced traction, and increased risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Cracking on the sidewall of the front tire
